document_data.Usages:
*In Cormyr, sherry was used to make sauce to serve [[lambs' kidneys]] in, alongside [[chestnut]] and [[parsnip]] fritters.
*[[Blentra's cider and vinegar oyster sauce]] of [[Marsember]] was crafted using [[almond]] sherry.
*The infamous bracer, a cure for hangover called [[beef tea]] was made with a trace of brandy, sherry, or zzar.{{cite web| url = https://web.archive.org/web/20211028234155/http://candlekeep.com/downloads/So_Saith_Ed_Part25_%282010-2016%29.zip| title = So Saith Ed 2010-2016| accessdate = 25-11-2021| date = 25-11-2021}}
*Across [[Faerûn]], sherry was also used in making "laving sauces" served for dipping alongside [[giant spearfish]], and [[rock reef crab]].
*Sherries and herd-infused wines were a customary libation during [[Omaurae]], th [[Shieldmeet]]-related festivities of [[Silverymoon]], during which new plays were performed for the public.{{cite web| url = https://web.archive.org/web/20230619061514/https://candlekeep.com/library/articles/sse/sse_070809-05.htm| title = So Saith Ed Jul – Sep 2005| accessdate = 25-11-2021| date = 25-11-2021}}
